President Cyril Ramaphosa will be answering questions in the National Council of Provinces for the first time in the 6th administration. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa will be answering questions in the National Council of Provinces. Ramaphosa is expected to face questions including what feedback he’s received from the deputy president on the Eskom crisis and whether government has reviewed the stimulus package to revitalise and bolster job creation. READ: Five tough questions Ramaphosa will face in Parliament He will answer questions on what plans are in place to professionalise and train police to improve quality of investigations into Gender-based violence. The President will also brief the NCOP on whether strategic interventions have been developed to protect domestic industries from global trade wars.